            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/fantastic-four-galactus-popcorn-bucket-switch-2-sales-1851784491<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="ea9a7e91117275e885fb58e2021e0183" data-recommend-id="image://ea9a7e91117275e885fb58e2021e0183" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Build A Rocket Boy / ExtraEmily / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / AMC / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Wizards of the Coast / Joshua Raphael<!-- -->, <!-- -->1047 Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ea9a7e91117275e885fb58e2021e0183" data-recommend-id="image://ea9a7e91117275e885fb58e2021e0183" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>It’s a little funny to consider the following stories “news” given the state of the world right now. I’m tempted to explain what I mean by that, but I’m just as happy to let that sentence be an inkblot test, revealing just what type of person you are based on the first thing that pops into your mind. (If the thought of that angers you, then I guess you have your answer.)</p><p>Nevertheless, read on for very important information about expensive popcorn buckets, Switch 2 settings (and astronomical sales), a disastrous launch week for <em>MindsEye</em>, an editorial revolt at Wikipedia over AI (okay, that one actually is kind of important), and more.</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="a1b624a1776f499a0f48a8fa439e3518" data-recommend-id="image://a1b624a1776f499a0f48a8fa439e3518" data-format="png" data-width="1910" data-height="1074" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 sits on the grass. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 sits on the grass. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a1b624a1776f499a0f48a8fa439e3518" data-recommend-id="image://a1b624a1776f499a0f48a8fa439e3518" data-format="png" data-width="1910" data-height="1074" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Switch 2 sits on the grass. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>The Switch 2 <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-review-best-things-list-hate-love-nintendo-1851783873&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-review-best-things-list-hate-love-nintendo-1851783873">has a ton of new features</a></span> and a much more detailed list of settings you can tinker with than its predecessor. Here are four you should change right from the jump to improve your overall experience with Nintendo’s new <em>Mario Kart World</em> machine. Just go into the settings menu inside the gear icon near the bottom right of the home screen to get started.  - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-settings-hdr-charging-internet-sleep-mode-1851784149?_gl=1*dizj4m*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-settings-hdr-charging-internet-sleep-mode-1851784149?_gl=1*dizj4m*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="aa09b256615c422f7d1e1535d023e578" data-recommend-id="image://aa09b256615c422f7d1e1535d023e578" data-format="png" data-width="1623" data-height="911" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A streamer watches their car explode. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A streamer watches their car explode. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Build A Rocket Boy / ExtraEmily / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="aa09b256615c422f7d1e1535d023e578" data-recommend-id="image://aa09b256615c422f7d1e1535d023e578" data-format="png" data-width="1623" data-height="911" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A streamer watches their car explode. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><em>MindsEye</em> is the first new game from longtime <em>Grand Theft Auto</em> producer Leslie Benzies and his studio Build A Rocket Boy, and it’s not going well. After tons of pre-launch red flags, the techno thriller shooter is now out in the wild and suffering all the day-one woes: bugs, poor optimization on PC, and underlying gameplay that early players say is barely passable for a big release in 2025. “Build A Rocket Boy, I genuinely wanted you to pull this off,” wrote one Steam user. “Sadly, this game plays like crap.” - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mindseye-steam-reviews-bugs-glitches-update-refunds-1851784312?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mindseye-steam-reviews-bugs-glitches-update-refunds-1851784312?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c7c339c86b0b93d01f7a6867a62247c0" data-recommend-id="image://c7c339c86b0b93d01f7a6867a62247c0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / AMC / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c7c339c86b0b93d01f7a6867a62247c0" data-recommend-id="image://c7c339c86b0b93d01f7a6867a62247c0" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="3b189589df018cfa4b7827ff71f2ea39" data-recommend-id="image://3b189589df018cfa4b7827ff71f2ea39" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario with dollars for eyes." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Mario with dollars for eyes." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Nintendo / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="3b189589df018cfa4b7827ff71f2ea39" data-recommend-id="image://3b189589df018cfa4b7827ff71f2ea39" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Mario with dollars for eyes." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>We already knew the Nintendo Switch 2 was going to sell well. Demand has been feisty, and <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-preorder-walmart-target-best-buy-nintendo-1851777604&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-preorder-walmart-target-best-buy-nintendo-1851777604">pre-orders sold out extraordinarily quickly</a></span>. Nintendo now reports that it was even more popular than bad been expected, selling 3.5 million consoles in the first four days. For context, the original Switch took a month to sell 2.75 million units. - John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-sales-fastest-selling-console-ever-1851784293?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-2-sales-fastest-selling-console-ever-1851784293?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="1b11a14f1b0882a941547802c0e9edc4" data-recommend-id="image://1b11a14f1b0882a941547802c0e9edc4" data-format="png" data-width="1573" data-height="886" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Clive holds up his sword. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Clive holds up his sword. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Wizards of the Coast / Joshua Raphael</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1b11a14f1b0882a941547802c0e9edc4" data-recommend-id="image://1b11a14f1b0882a941547802c0e9edc4" data-format="png" data-width="1573" data-height="886" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Clive holds up his sword. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="e0f1444cd519b8030c9141ce8ef3de86" data-recommend-id="image://e0f1444cd519b8030c9141ce8ef3de86" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ian Proulx makes faces. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Ian Proulx makes faces. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->1047 Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="e0f1444cd519b8030c9141ce8ef3de86" data-recommend-id="image://e0f1444cd519b8030c9141ce8ef3de86" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ian Proulx makes faces. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>An unusual email hit my inbox earlier today. It was from PR for the makers of <em>Splitgate 2</em>, a free-to-play portal shooter that released just a few days ago and stirred up drama with <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/splitgate-2-battle-royale-trump-hat-summer-game-fest-1851783949&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/splitgate-2-battle-royale-trump-hat-summer-game-fest-1851783949">a MAGA-infused meme at Summer Game Fest</a></span> from studio head Ian Proulx. “The CEO of 1047 Games has issued a video statement and apology to the community and gaming fans for his ‘Make FPS Great Again’ hat during Summer Games Fest,” the email read. It offered interviews.  - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/splitgate-2-apology-video-maga-hat-ranked-battle-royale-1851784272?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/splitgate-2-apology-video-maga-hat-ranked-battle-royale-1851784272?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ea8a2a27669acaa6724f64ff4db87c57" data-recommend-id="image://ea8a2a27669acaa6724f64ff4db87c57" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Wikipedia globe placed on Homer Simpson's head as he leads an angry mob because AI sucks" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The Wikipedia globe placed on Homer Simpson's head as he leads an angry mob because AI sucks" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ea8a2a27669acaa6724f64ff4db87c57" data-recommend-id="image://ea8a2a27669acaa6724f64ff4db87c57" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The Wikipedia globe placed on Homer Simpson's head as he leads an angry mob because AI sucks" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>The Wikimedia Foundation, a nonprofit group that hosts, develops, and controls <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/barbenheimer-barbie-oppenheimer-meme-wikipedia-war-1850664668&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/barbenheimer-barbie-oppenheimer-meme-wikipedia-war-1850664668">Wikipedia</a></span>, has announced that it won’t be moving forward with plans to add AI-generated summaries to articles after it received an overwhelmingly negative reaction from its army of dedicated (and unpaid) human editors.  - Zack Zwiezen </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/wikipedia-ai-generated-plan-slop-summaries-editors-yell-1851784353?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/wikipedia-ai-generated-plan-slop-summaries-editors-yell-1851784353?_gl=1*1tptgmm*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NDIyMCRqOSRsMCRoMA..">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
